}}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== There does not appear to be a v1 version of this model. Hooray.
The F9K1119v1 AC1600 shares the same FCC ID as this model, which the FCC ''Application'' lists as ''AC1750 DB Wi-Fi Dual-Band AC + Gigabit Router, AC1600 DB Wi-Fi Dual-Band AC + Gigabit Router''
Per the FCC photos... *The WiSoC used is a QCA9558-AT4A. *The QCA9880 (QCA9880-2R4E / QCA9880v2 [???]) wireless module appears to be using three '''Skyworks''' SE5003L1 / 5003L1 5 GHz Power Amplifier modules. **"EW-7933MAC V1.0A" and "P/C:C71-011" is silkscreened on the back of the wireless module, implying that the module is an '''Edimax''' EW-7933MAC. **There is also a manuf. P/N of some sort on the board.. but it is not readable in the provided photos. I will, however, presume <small>('''erroneously?''')</small> that '''Edimax''' is indeed manufacturing this device ('''EW-7933AC''' ??)... *An '''EtronTech''' EJ168A USB 3.0 controller is on-board.. providing the device with two USB 3.0 ports. *The GbE Switch is a QCA8337-AL3C. Per additional FCC docs... *The device is using '''Airgain''' PCB antennas. **1x N2420S-T10-B100S2 (3.4 dBi gain @ 2.4 GHz) **1x N2420S-T10-W50S2 (3.9 dBi gain @ 2.4 GHz) **1x N2420S-T10-G190S2 (4.4 dBi gain @ 2.4 GHz) **1x N5x20B-T1-B150U (5.8 dBi gain @ 5 GHz) **1x N5x20B-T-G65U (5.3 dBi gain @ 5 GHz) **1x N5x20B-T-W85U (5.3 dBi gain @ 5 GHz) *A '''Macronix''' Serial Flash is on the back of the board.
The default SSID patterns are '''belkin.{last three LAN MAC hex digits}''' and the 5 GHz radio could be suffixed with '''.5GHz''' or '''.media'''
The power adapter shown in the FCC external photos is a ('''Belkin''' branded) '''DVE''' DSA-30PFB-12 FUS 120250 (100-240VAC ~ 50/60 Hz, 0.8A -> 12VDC, 2.5A).
